parameters: Celis, the Gale Wind: You've come a long way.
Clea: Indeed, it was far from Photizona.
Celis, the Gale Wind: Hehe, that's not it.

Celis, the Gale Wind: Clea was a girl who had never even
held a sword. But now she can fight, and she has many
comrades who will fight alongside her.

Celis, the Gale Wind: That's impressive and makes me really
happy.
Clea: Celis-san... Thank you very much!

Celis, the Gale Wind: I'm the one who wants to say thank
you... Thank you for standing up and coming to the guild.

Celis, the Gale Wind: Thank you for staying alive. I want to
express my gratitude for surviving from now on.

Celis, the Gale Wind: If Clea can achieve her goal and have
a dream that she passionately pursues from the bottom of her
heart--

Clea: At that time, I will be the first to tell you, Celis-
san, about your dream as well.

Celis, the Gale Wind: Yes, I'm looking forward to it, you
know?
Celis, the Gale Wind: It's about time to return Clea.

Celis, the Gale Wind: Just like everyone else, Clea is an
important presence to me.
Celis, the Gale Wind: Take care of Clea, everyone.
Mage Relm: ...Finally, it's time to defeat the dragon.
Priestess Sophia: Oh my, is Relm-chan feeling anxious?

Mage Relm: As the genius that I am...! Ugh, yes, I'm feeling
anxious, dragons are scary, you know!

Thief Nora: Ah, I'm scared too~! I'm really anxious about
what comes after.

Thief Nora: What about after defeating the dragon? Can I
really join up with everyone in the thief guild?

Thief Nora: I feel like I'll become useless again if I
separate from everyone...

Priestess Sophia: Indeed, it is a source of concern. I too
am unsure if I can change my way of life...

Mage Relm: A-And it's okay to stay as friends, right? We
belong to different organizations, have different goals, and
we'll be separated...
Mage Relm: But, is it okay for us to stay as friends...?

Clea: Of course. We will always be comrades. I think of us
as friends who will always come running if something
happens.

Thief Nora: Yes, me too! Everyone here is my first group of
friends!
Priestess Sophia: Hehe, were you worried about that?

Mage Relm: Y-You're so noisy! I'm just a bit worried because
I'm not familiar with normal people's friendships!

Priestess Sophia: Oh my, such rough words... It's terrible
to say that to a friend... *sniffle*...

Clea: Let's return soon. Once the night is over, it will be
time for the decisive battle...
Clea (Father, Mother... Clea has come this far)

Clea (I will definitely succeed in avenging with my
comrades...!)
